docs.abstract: Voice-activated helpers can automate life’s little chores, once you get the hang of them.
docs.snippet: Voice-activated helpers can automate life’s little chores, once you get the hang of them.
docs.lead_paragraph: Apple added its Siri assistant to the iPhone 4S model in 2011, giving users a hand-free way to schedule appointments, play music, look up information and perform other basic tasks. Less than a decade later, digital assistants are in a plethora of digital devices, including computers, smart speakers, dashboards and watches, and they can help you ease into the day and keep the household running smoothly.

headline.main: Put Alexa and Siri to Work
headline.print_headline: Getting the Most From Your Digital Helper

docs.abstract: The Seattle Seahawks’ coach is shaping his locker room talks about self-discovery and finding meaning in life for corporate America.
docs.snippet: The Seattle Seahawks’ coach is shaping his locker room talks about self-discovery and finding meaning in life for corporate America.
docs.lead_paragraph: Pete Carroll has heard the haters telling him what he can do with all his New Age banter, all that talk about self-discovery and the Seattle Seahawks’ culture of love.

headline.main: Pete Carroll Wants to Change Your Life
headline.print_headline: Pete Carroll Wants to Change Your Life

docs.abstract: The intelligence agency alerted Microsoft to a vulnerability in Windows. Typically, it would keep quiet and exploit the flaw.
docs.snippet: The intelligence agency alerted Microsoft to a vulnerability in Windows. Typically, it would keep quiet and exploit the flaw.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The National Security Agency has taken a significant step toward protecting the world’s computer systems, announcing Tuesday that it alerted Microsoft to a vulnerability in its Windows operating system rather than following the agency’s typical approach of keeping quiet and exploiting the flaw to develop cyberweapons.

headline.main: N.S.A. Takes Step Toward Protecting World’s Computers, Not Just Hacking Them
headline.print_headline: Seeing Digital Flaw, N.S.A. Decides to Warn, Not Snoop

byline.original: By Julian E. Barnes and David E. Sanger
